             My father is a <rs id="t18091101-84-viclabel525" type="occupation">publican</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18091101-84-victim696 t18091101-84-viclabel525"></join> in <placeName id="t18091101-84-crimeloc526">Whitechapel Road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18091101-84-crimeloc526" type="placeName" value="Whitechapel Road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18091101-84-crimeloc526" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18091101-84-off523 t18091101-84-crimeloc526"></join>, on the 8th of October, the prisoner came to our house to lodge, he came down in the morning, he asked for a glass of gin; he could not drink it his hands shook so; my mother suspected him, she looked behind his coat, and saw a sheet in his breeches; my mother let him go out, and sent me up stairs, he had doubled one sheet to make it look like two; I went after him, and brought him back, he pulled the sheet out of his breeches himself.</p>
               <p>The property produced and identified.</p>
               <p>The prisoner said nothing in his defence, nor called any witnesses to character.</p>
               <p>
